name: Dragon Ball: Sparking! Zero
summary: Dragon Ball Sparking! Zero has received mixed reviews from critics. While some have praised the game's free-form fighting system, others have criticized its repetitive missions and story mode. IGN said the game is "a solid entry in the Dragon Ball fighting game series", but criticized its "lack of polish". PC Gamer praised the game's "fluid combat", but said the game "doesn't do enough to differentiate itself from other Dragon Ball fighting games". Shacknews called the game "a fun and engaging fighting game that will please fans of the Dragon Ball series". TheGamer said the game is "a worthy successor to the Tenkaichi series", but criticized its "short campaign". Men's Journal said the game "is still missing the magic of Budokai Tenkaichi 3". GAMINGbible said the game "is the wish we've all been waiting for". Digital Trends said the game is "an incredible fighting sandbox that stumbles on story". MonsterVine said the game is "Budokai Tenkaichi's triumphant return". VG247 said the game is "as meaningful a send-up to the source material as one could hope for".

name: Gary Ruvkun
summary: American scientists Victor Ambros and Gary Ruvkun have been awarded the Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine for their groundbreaking discovery of microRNAs, a class of small molecules that regulate gene expression. Ruvkun, a scientist at Harvard Medical School, and Ambros, a professor at the University of Massachusetts Medical School, made their discovery using the roundworm Caenorhabditis elegans as a model organism. Their work has revolutionized the understanding of gene regulation, providing insights into a wide range of biological processes and diseases.

summary: Eric Roberts has released a memoir titled "Regret," which he spent months editing and correcting. In the book, he offers marriage advice to his "Dancing with the Stars" (DWTS) partners Britt Stewart and Daniel Durant. Despite their sibling relationship, Julia Roberts reportedly will never speak to Eric again due to him using her life to sell his book. The 44-year-old Matthew Eric Roberts has passed away. Eric Roberts has overcome addiction and is currently on "DWTS" while promoting his new book. While some question whether Anna Delvey's appearance on "DWTS" was appropriate, Eric Roberts offers marriage advice to his DWTS partners. summary: Florida has a history of facing powerful Category 5 hurricanes, with Milton being the latest storm to pose a significant threat. Milton is projected to maintain its extreme danger as it makes landfall in Florida, comparable to the devastating impacts of previous Category 5 hurricanes like Andrew, Ian, and Michael. While the exact strength of Milton upon landfall remains uncertain, it is crucial to assess its potential impact in relation to other historic hurricanes that have affected the United States mainland. By comparing Milton to previous Category 5 storms, experts and officials can gain insights into the potential damage and necessary preparedness measures to mitigate the storm's effects.

name: Columbus Day
summary: As Columbus Day approaches, cities across the United States are preparing for celebrations and commemorations. In Indiana, certain closures will be in effect on the holiday. In Chicago, ABC7 will broadcast a parade celebrating Italian American Heritage Month. New York City's 80th annual Columbus Day Parade will return to honor Italian-American heritage. Union County, New Jersey, will hold a flag-raising ceremony. While some debate the appropriateness of Columbus Day given Christopher Columbus's controversial legacy, others argue for maintaining a day off in October. In Yonkers, New York, the Columbus Day Parade will be held with revelers enjoying festivities. The Californian explores the status of Columbus Day and Indigenous Peoples' Day as federal holidays, while Visit Philadelphia highlights events for Indigenous Peoples' Day Weekend. These events and announcements reflect the ongoing discussions and recognition of both Italian American heritage and Indigenous perspectives during this time of year.
